                <h1>Does Pretrial Diversion Appear on Background Checks?</h1>
                <p>Pretrial diversion programs, which offer alternatives to traditional prosecution, usually do not show up on background checks when successfully completed. This is because they are designed to prevent a criminal record. However, specifics can vary by jurisdiction, so it's essential to check local laws to understand how they handle these records.</p>
